excerpt: Water sports & diving to a submerged village are popular at this lake created by damming a river.
detail_description: Paranoá Lake, formed by damming a river, is a popular destination for water sports and diving. Visitors can enjoy activities such as water skiing, wakeboarding, sailing, rowing, and even diving to explore the submerged village of Vila Amaury. The lake also offers lakeside restaurants for waterfront dining and a park for recreation. Additionally, the area features modernist architecture like Brasilia Cathedral and other natural and man-made attractions to explore.
name: Paranoá Lake
address: Brasília - Federal District, Brazil

excerpt: Church distinguished by its blue floor-to-ceiling windows on all sides & a huge Murano chandelier.
detail_description: Santuário São João Bosco is a unique church dedicated to the 19th-century Italian priest, with an interior defined by striking blue Murano glass windows and a grand chandelier. The building, located on the 15th parallel, was designed by architect Vasconcelos Naves and features tall pointed arches framing stained glass windows in various shades of blue.
name: Santuário São João Bosco
address: Quadra 702 Sul Bloco B, SHCS, Brasília - DF, Brazil

excerpt: Oscar Niemeyer–designed museum with exhibits about former Brazilian president Juscelino Kubitschek.
detail_description: Memorial JK is a museum in Brasilia designed by Oscar Niemeyer, dedicated to the former Brazilian president Juscelino Kubitschek. The memorial was inaugurated in 1981 and features a 28-meter statue of Juscelino, along with exhibits showcasing his life and legacy. Visitors can explore the Mortuary Chamber, where Juscelino's remains are housed, as well as personal objects and presidential memorabilia.
name: Memorial JK
address: Eixo Monumental - Lado Oeste, Praça do Cruzeiro, Brasília - DF, 70070-300, Brazil

excerpt: Cultural center with a modern, stilted design housing contemporary art galleries, a cinema & a cafe.
detail_description: Located in Brasília, Centro Cultural Banco do Brasil is a modern cultural center with a unique stilted design. It houses contemporary art galleries, a cinema, and a cafe. The city itself is known for its significance in Legal Tourism due to being the center of the nation's three powers. Visitors can explore this cultural hub which hosts various exhibitions, events, and concerts including the Cinema Festival and Japanese Festival.
name: Centro Cultural Banco do Brasil - Brasília
address: Asa sul Trecho 2 - Brasília, DF, 70200-002, Brazil

excerpt: Modern Roman Catholic church designed by Niemeyer in 1970 & containing stained glass & sculptures.
detail_description: The Cathedral of Brasília, designed by Niemeyer in 1970, is a modern Roman Catholic church that stands as one of the most impressive structures in Brazil's capital city. Situated between the ministries and downtown rodoviaria, it commemorates the inauguration of Brasília with its unique design resembling an inverted chalice and crown of thorns. The sunken nave creates an unusual layout where most of the interior floor is below ground level.
name: Catedral Metropolitana Nossa Senhora Aparecida
address: Esplanada dos Ministérios lote 12 - Brasília, DF, 70050-000, Brazil

excerpt: Modern, Oscar Niemeyer-designed complex housing Brazil's legislature & featuring tours & exhibits.
detail_description: The National Congress in Brasilia is a modern complex designed by the renowned architect Oscar Niemeyer. It houses Brazil's legislature and offers tours and exhibits for visitors. The building consists of a flat-based structure with two tall buildings, one for the Chamber of Deputies and the other for the Senate, featuring distinctive architectural elements. Guided tours provide insight into the political processes and allow visitors to observe congress sessions in progress, offering a unique glimpse into one of the world's largest democracies.
name: Congresso Nacional
address: Palácio do Congresso Nacional - Praça dos 3 Poderes, Brasília - DF, 70160-900, Brazil

detail_description: The Torre de TV de Brasília, inspired by the Eiffel Tower, stands at 75 meters and offers panoramic views of the city. It is one of Brasilia's modernist structures and provides an excellent vantage point to appreciate the city's unique layout. Visitors can access the tower for free and enjoy stunning views of Plano Piloto, especially at night when the city lights are on. The tower also features a water fountain that adds to its charm.
name: Torre de TV de Brasília
address: Brasilia TV Tower, Esplanada da Torre - Plano Piloto, Brasília - DF, 70070-300, Brazil

excerpt: 69,000-acre park offering an array of indigenous plant & bird species, plus a natural swimming hole.
detail_description: Parque Nacional de Brasília, covering 28,000 hectares in the northwest part of the city, is a 69,000-acre park that offers an array of indigenous plant and bird species. The park features two trails: the Capivara trail and the Cristal Agua trail.
name: Parque Nacional de Brasília
address: BR-450, EPIA Norte, Zona Industrial, Brasília - DF, 70635-800, Brazil

excerpt: Centered on its namesake white stone plaza with a vast Brazilian flag, Praça dos Três Poderes, or PTP, is known for its monumental modernist ensemble of Oscar Niemeyer-designed buildings. The Planalto Palace, housing the presidential offices, the Supremo Tribunal Federal high court, and the National Congress parliament are all open for tours. Crowded by day with government employees, the area is quiet at night.
detail_description: Praça dos Três Poderes, also known as PTP, is a striking white stone plaza featuring the monumental modernist architectural ensemble designed by Oscar Niemeyer. The area is home to significant government buildings such as the Planalto Palace, which houses the presidential offices, the Supremo Tribunal Federal high court, and the National Congress parliament. During the day, it bustles with government employees and visitors exploring these iconic structures.
name: Praça dos Três Poderes
address: Brasília, Federal District, Brazil

detail_description: Parque da Cidade is a great place to extend your running route, as it can be combined with the adjacent Monumental Axis route or Asa Norte for a longer run. It offers an opportunity for runners to add extra distance and explore more of the surrounding areas.
name: Parque da Cidade
address: Srps - Brasília, DF, 70655-775, Brazil

excerpt: Brasília, inaugurated as Brazil’s capital in 1960, is a planned city distinguished by its white, modern architecture, chiefly designed by Oscar Niemeyer. Laid out in the shape of an airplane, its “fuselage” is the Monumental Axis, 2 wide avenues flanking a massive park. In the “cockpit” is Praça dos Três Poderes, named for the 3 branches of government surrounding it.
detail_description: Brasília, established as Brazil's capital in 1960, is a meticulously planned city renowned for its modern white architecture, primarily crafted by Oscar Niemeyer. The city is laid out in the shape of an airplane, with the Monumental Axis serving as its 'fuselage,' flanked by two broad avenues and a vast park. At the heart of this layout lies Praça dos Três Poderes, named after the three government branches that encompass it.
name: Brasília
address: Federal District, Brazil

excerpt: Architecturally unique bridge with 3 intertwined arches each holding up a section of the roadway.
detail_description: The Juscelino Kubitschek Bridge, also known as the President Bridge or JK Bridge, is a remarkable architectural feat located in Brasilia, Brazil. Spanning Lake Paranoa, this bridge features three intertwined arches that support the roadway and stand at over 60 meters in height. Designed by architect Alexandre Chan as part of a project to revitalize the area and improve traffic congestion, it has become an iconic landmark in the city.
name: Juscelino Kubitschek Bridge
address: Brasília - DF, Brazil

excerpt: Iconic white-domed building by Oscar Niemeyer hosting art exhibitions & cultural events.
detail_description: The MUSEU Nacional da República is a significant center for Brazilian history and culture, housed in an iconic white-domed building designed by Oscar Niemeyer. The museum features a vast collection of historical documents, photographs, artifacts, and museum pieces that narrate the history of Brazil since the Proclamation of the Republic. Visitors can enjoy guided tours, educational programs, lectures, and other activities within this architectural marvel.
name: MUSEU Nacional da República
address: Setor Cultural Sul, Lote 2 próximo à Rodoviária do Plano Piloto, Brasília - DF, 70070-150, Brazil

detail_description: Praça dos Três Poderes Panteão da Pátria e da Liberdade Tancredo Neves in Brasília showcases modernist architecture, with its design resembling a dove. The three floors of the building pay tribute to individuals who have made significant contributions to the Brazilian homeland. Their names are inscribed in the Livro de Aço, granting them the title of national hero.
name: Praça dos Três Poderes Panteão da Pátria e da Liberdade Tancredo Neves - Brasília
address: DF, Brazil

excerpt: A trendy, upscale restaurant serving traditional & reinvented Northeastern Brazilian dishes.
detail_description: Mangai is a renowned upscale restaurant that offers traditional and reinvented Northeastern Brazilian dishes. Located near the JK Bridge, it boasts impressive architecture and can accommodate up to 900 patrons. Originally a family farmhouse, it has evolved into a vast buffet restaurant serving food by the kilo. Specializing in cuisine from Brazil's Northeast, Mangai offers an extensive buffet featuring dishes like carne de sol com nata and gororoba de camarao.
name: Mangai
address: SCE Sul, s/n - Lote 2, Asa Sul, Brasília - DF, 70200-002, Brazil

excerpt: Building featuring the presidential office & circa-1960 modern design by Oscar Neimeyer, with tours.
detail_description: Palácio do Planalto, located in Brasilia, Brazil, is an elegant modernist building designed by Oscar Niemeyer and serves as the official workplace of the country's president. The structure dates back to 1958 and features stylish curved columns fronted by a large pool. Situated at Praca dos Tres Poderes (Three Powers Square), it is part of a complex that includes four additional buildings.
name: Palácio do Planalto
address: Praça dos Três Poderes - Brasília, DF, 70150-900, Brazil

excerpt: Handmade Brazilian crafts & furniture are offered at this expansive fair with food stalls.
detail_description: Nestled at the base of the iconic TV Tower, the Feira da Torre de TV is a vibrant hub of creativity and culture that showcases the best of Brazilian craftsmanship. This expansive market features an array of handmade goods, from intricate jewelry to stylish clothing and unique home decor. As you stroll through its neatly arranged stalls, you'll also encounter tempting food stands offering mouthwatering traditional Brazilian dishes.
name: Feira da Torre de TV
address: Feira de Artesanato da Torre de TV SDC, Eixo Monumental, Brasília - DF, 70070-350, Brazil

excerpt: Well-known spacious steakhouse with prime cuts of meat, assorted grilled dishes & a buffet.
detail_description: Fogo de Chão Brasília is a renowned and spacious steakhouse offering an array of prime meat cuts, grilled dishes, and a buffet. As part of the traditional rodizio continuous meal service, the restaurant's attentive waitstaff serves up to 18 different types of meat, including Southern Brazilian specialties like picanha top sirloin and fraldinha grilled bottom sirloin.
name: Fogo de Chão Brasília
address: ST DE CLUBES ESPORTIVOS SUL, Asa Sul Trecho 2, 2/11, Brasília - DF, 70200-002, Brazil

excerpt: The 4th tallest structure in Brazil, this TV broadcast tower was erected in 1967 & later modified.
detail_description: Brasilia TV Tower, the fourth tallest structure in Brazil, was built in 1967 and later underwent modifications. Located within a 20-minute walk from central Brasilia, it offers easy access to the city's attractions. Visitors can take a stroll to the observation deck and enjoy panoramic views of Brasilia from a unique vantage point. Whether you're an avid photographer or simply seeking a new perspective on the city, this is an ideal spot to witness Brasilia unfold beneath you.
name: Brasilia TV Tower
address: Brasília, DF, 70655-775, Brazil

excerpt: Iconic, Oscar Niemayer-designed building housing the country's highest court of appeal.
detail_description: The Supremo Tribunal Federal is housed in a renowned edifice created by famed architect Oscar Niemayer. It serves as the topmost court of appeal for the country, with authority over constitutional matters and cases involving high-ranking officials. The building's iconic design represents Brazil's modernist architectural style, featuring sweeping curves and sharp angles that make it a standout structure in the capital city.
name: Supremo Tribunal Federal
address: Praça dos Três Poderes - Brasília, DF, 70175-900, Brazil
